ABDOMEN (
Fig. 9A–C
). Tergites and sternites undivided; tergal chaetotaXy: 6:6:8:7:8:8:8:8:8:8:8:2; sternal chaetotaXy: 6:6:8:9:9:8:10:7:5:2; pleural membrane granulate anteriorly near cephalothoraX, granulo-striate posteriorly; without setae.

GENITALIA (
Fig. 13D
). Male genitalia with a small rounded ejaculatory opening, setal arrangement ca 5 setae situated anterior to opening.

LEGS (
Fig. 12A–B
). All legs with tarsus longer than metatarsus; femora slightly shorter than patella of leg I–II; scarcely granulate; femur + patella of leg IV 2 times as long as broad; legs III and IV with articulation between femur and patella slightly oblique; arolium shorter than claws, distally broadened and undivided; claws simple and not serrate.

